data.description: Panoramic mountain and valley views envelope this 4,328 sq ft/ 4 bed/ 3.5 bath home on 19.83 acres. Single level living begins with an expansive master bedroom with its own den/office and en suite. The walk-out basement has a kitchen, dining area, living room with fireplace, 3 bedrooms, and 2 full bathrooms. Favorite features of the home include the wine room, attached 3-car garage, and fully insulated and heated 2,300 sq ft shop with 14' RV door and standard bay door. The outside of the home has a 3-stall loafing shed with electric, lights, and heated water ready to accept your horses. There is mature landscaping, underground sprinklers, partial fencing, decks and covered patios decorating the home. Sit outside, enjoy the views, watch your horses run. Ride one down through the 2,000 acres of common space that the GRR residents enjoy to the 2.5 miles of ranch-private river access or the square mile of ranch-private hunting. This home has an assumable loan with an interest rate lower than today's rates.
